+++++ Special Containment Procedures:
All instances of SCP-x005 are to be housed in standard human containment cells, especially those displaying additional anomalous traits. Despite these measures, the sheer quantity of SCP-x005 instances has exceeded the Foundation's capacity to contain. As a result, knowledge of SCP-x005 has disseminated beyond controlled channels and is now considered publicly accessible information.

+++++ Description: 
SCP-x005 stands as the defining deviation from established Foundation protocol, as it is the first anomaly to be assigned a clearance level of 0 and it is the first and only documented instance of a full-scale breach of the Veil. The existence of SCP-x005 has necessitated an ongoing reassessment of containment doctrine and information control strategies. 

SCP-x005 is a human (Homo sapiens) woman with pale skin, blonde hair, and green eyes. SCP-x005, formerly known as Katelyn Connors displays no anomalous traits and is by all standards of measurement, an ordinary human woman. 

SCP-x005 was the victim of incident [[[CYA-009-19]]], in which [*https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-2000 SCP-2000] was activated by [DATA EXPUNGED] and began creating copies of the original Ms. Connors. At the time of writing, instances of SCP-x005 make up half of the human population.

SCP-x005 instances can vary wildly in form, due to [DATA EXPUNGED] during the incident. Most instances of SCP-x005 resemble the original Katelyn Connors, with pale skin, blonde hair, and green eyes. While most instances of SCP-x005 are non-anomalous in nature, outside of being exact replicas of the original SCP-x005, many instances are. A majority of these anomalies are reserved to physical appearances, such as animal-human hybrids, various non-human skin colors, and the appearance of auxiliary body parts such as gills, antennae, or teeth.



